Job Summary:

We are seeking a People & Culture (P&C) Analyst based in Canada(ideally Montreal) to provide Operational & Analytical excellence in people processes, with an eye to fostering a workplace culture, that supports equity, diversity and inclusiveness. This role will report to Senior Manager, People & Culture, with a primary focus on analyzing and drawing insights out of the HR data to help inform decision-making around our people investments. In addition, this role will provide superior customer service, as a front-line representative to our team members, and coordinate a variety of People & Culture tasks & initiatives.

Responsibilities:

Lead and manage day-to- day P&C operations and support our employees including responding to internal inquiries, administering HRIS & benefits, onboarding, offboarding, carrying out organizational policies and practices, and upholding organizational culture;
Lead the HR analytics process through its monthly, quarterly and annual cycle, including preparing and leading relevant review and analysis;
Help in providing relevant data, statistics, trends, and patterns to make the HR key processes more efficient;
Support the management of our P&C scorecard in terms of regular reporting and build/ evolve our leading and lagging indicator;
Support the management of the compensation & benefit analysis and audit process, drives the quarterly internal & external benchmark and works closely with the P&C leadership to provide related insights & forecast;
Provide timely and accurate transactional support for employee life cycle events through partnering with the business and internal P&C teams (e.g. Onboarding, Offboarding, HRIS, Payroll and others);
Provide excellent customer service support both internally and externally to HR and triage inquiries beyond self-serve portal;
Partner with internal teams and stakeholders to support P&C program administration and initiatives;
Maintain knowledge of organizational and departmental policies and procedures to answer general employee and leader inquiries;
Assist with the creation of materials related to P&C procedures and policies (e.g. process documentation, FAQs, etc.);
Support P&C programs such as annual compensation cycles, performance & development reviews, benefit enrolment and others;
Actively participate in projects to develop, review and improve P&C processes.

Qualifications:

College Degree or Diploma in Human Resources, or equivalent with working experience in relevant field, ideally minimum of 3+ years;
Working knowledge of various database management and HRIS systems;
Systematic knowledge and understanding of key HR processes, their effects on the inner working of the HR department, and how to manage them;
Complete knowledge of data analysis techniques, tools, and software;
Strong research and analytical skills, to conduct primary and secondary research, as well as effectively analyze the accumulated data;
Proficient with Microsoft Excel, Microsoft PowerPoint, and other Microsoft Office applications;
Working experience in and navigating various platforms and HRIS systems;
Ability to work autonomously, collaboratively and multi-task many priorities in a fast paced, project-oriented business;
Ability to work with rigid deadlines while maintaining a high degree of accuracy and attention to detail;
Demonstrated previous experience developing strong relationships across all levels of the organization with the ability to influence;
Excellent written and oral communication skills;
Bilingual (English & French) is preferred.

